typing_extensions
-----------------
File:     .claude-plugin/scripts/_vendor/typing_extensions.py
Upstream: https://github.com/python/typing_extensions
Version:  4.15.0 (PyPI typing_extensions-4.15.0; git tag 4.15.0)
Licence:  PSF-2.0 (Python Software Foundation License, version 2)

The `typing_extensions` backport module, vendored directly as a single
top-level module (an attribution header is prepended; the body below it
is a byte-faithful copy of the upstream 4.15.0 distribution). The
host-side dispatcher import path needs `assert_never`
(cross_repo/resolve.py) and `override` (commands/_otel_receive.py); on
the Python 3.10 target (requires-python >= 3.10.16) both live only in
typing_extensions, not stdlib `typing`. Vendoring lets the flattened
plugin cache satisfy those imports with no `uv sync` and no apt
`python3-typing-extensions`.

